summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of East Alder Street, from Thirty-second Avenue to Thrity-third Avenue and Thirty-third Avenue from East Alder Street to the south line of Leshi Heights Addition, all in the City of Seattle, by constructing concrete walks, all in accordance with Resolution No. 2309 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle
